        // A diagonal move changes (x,y) to (x+dx, y+dy) where dx, dy are non-zero.
        // (x+dx) + (y+dy) has different parity than x+y if dx, dy are both odd (which they are, +/-1).
        // So, a diagonal move flips the parity of (x+y).
        // A straight move changes (x,y) to (x+dx, y) or (x, y+dy) where one of dx, dy is zero.
        // (x+dx)+y or x+(y+dy) has different parity than x+y if dx or dy is odd (which they are, +/-1).
        // So, a straight move also flips the parity of (x+y).
